cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.AI 

This paper is about improving the state-of-the-art in collaborative filtering, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new model for recommendation based on graph convolution network (GCN), which is a popular technique in both social network analysis (cs.SI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also compares its proposed model with existing GCN-based recommender models, which is a common task in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
